### Key Findings

**Codebase context** (already discovered — no API work needed):
- `ThingCard.tsx` already has a checkbox button for task-type items that calls `updateThing(thing.id, { active: false })` — but it only marks done (one-way), doesn't toggle, and removes the item after 600ms rather than animating to the bottom of the list
- The PATCH `/things/{id}` endpoint already supports `active: boolean` toggle
- State management is Zustand (not TanStack Query), so `useOptimistic` or local `useState` + try/catch rollback is the right pattern

**Animation patterns**:
- `text-decoration-line` (strikethrough) is **not CSS-transition-animatable** — it snaps on instantly. Apply `line-through` class immediately; animate `opacity` separately with `transition-opacity duration-300`
- Smooth animate-to-bottom requires the **FLIP technique**: snapshot `getBoundingClientRect()` before sort, sort the array (active first), then `requestAnimationFrame` + `transform: translateY()` to animate the transition. Alternatively, `framer-motion` `layout` prop handles this automatically

**Optimistic toggle**:
- `useOptimistic` (React 19) is the cleanest approach: flip the boolean immediately inside `startTransition`, auto-reverts on API failure
- If React version is < 19, use local `useState` + try/catch with explicit rollback

**Accessibility**:
- Use native `<input type="checkbox">` (not `<div role="checkbox">`) — handles `aria-checked`, Space-key, and focus ring natively
- Keep checkbox and title as separate click targets: `<input>` + `aria-label="Mark [title] as complete"`, and a sibling `<button>` for the title to open detail

### Gaps

- Need to verify React version in the project (`package.json`) to determine if `useOptimistic` is available
- The existing `ThingCard.tsx` checkbox is one-way only (marks done, never re-activates) — issue requires a true toggle
